{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":428,"text":"The world's largest and most devastating\nenvironmental and industrial project"},{"time":5733,"text":"is situated in the heart of the largest\nand most intact forest in the world,"},{"time":9598,"text":"Canada's boreal forest."},{"time":11426,"text":"It stretches right across\nNorthern Canada, in Labrador,"},{"time":15873,"text":"it's home to the largest remaining\nwild caribou herd in the world:"},{"time":19070,"text":"the George River caribou herd,"},{"time":20565,"text":"numbering approximately 400,000 animals."},{"time":22758,"text":"Unfortunately, when I was there,\nI couldn't find one of them,"},{"time":25640,"text":"but you have the antlers as proof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27949,"text":"All across the boreal,"},{"time":29351,"text":"we're blessed with this incredible\nabundance of wetlands."},{"time":32769,"text":"Wetlands, globally, are one\nof the most endangered ecosystems."},{"time":37126,"text":"They're absolutely critical ecosystems,"},{"time":40032,"text":"they clean air, they clean water,"},{"time":42637,"text":"they sequester large amounts\nof greenhouse gases,"},{"time":45730,"text":"and they're home\nto a huge diversity of species."},{"time":49155,"text":"In the boreal, they are also the home"},{"time":51536,"text":"where almost 50 percent of the 800 bird\nspecies found in North America"},{"time":55911,"text":"migrate north to breed\nand raise their young."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60571,"text":"In Ontario, the boreal marches down south\nto the north shore of Lake Superior."},{"time":66032,"text":"And these incredibly\nbeautiful boreal forests"},{"time":69569,"text":"were the inspiration for some of the most\nfamous art in Canadian history,"},{"time":73538,"text":"the Group of Seven\nwere very inspired by this landscape,"},{"time":77892,"text":"and so the boreal is not just a really key\npart of our natural heritage,"},{"time":83274,"text":"but also an important part\nof our cultural heritage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86566,"text":"In Manitoba, this is an image\nfrom the east side of Lake Winnipeg,"},{"time":90538,"text":"and this is the home of the newly\ndesignated UNESCO Cultural Heritage site."},{"time":96531,"text":"In Saskatchewan,\nas across all of the boreal,"},{"time":99573,"text":"home to some of our most famous rivers,"},{"time":102010,"text":"an incredible network of rivers and lakes\nthat every school-age child learns about,"},{"time":107090,"text":"the Peace, the Athabasca,\nthe Churchill here, the Mackenzie,"},{"time":111019,"text":"and these networks\nwere the historical routes"},{"time":114874,"text":"for the voyageur and the coureur de bois,"},{"time":117122,"text":"the first non-aboriginal\nexplorers of Northern Canada"},{"time":120453,"text":"that, taking from\nthe First Nations people,"},{"time":123236,"text":"used canoes and paddled to explore"},{"time":125640,"text":"for a trade route,\na Northwest Passage for the fur trade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129954,"text":"In the North, the boreal\nis bordered by the tundra,"},{"time":133609,"text":"and just below that, in Yukon,"},{"time":136656,"text":"we have this incredible valley,\nthe Tombstone Valley."},{"time":140158,"text":"And the Tombstone Valley is home\nto the Porcupine caribou herd."},{"time":144868,"text":"Now you've probably heard\nabout the Porcupine caribou herd"},{"time":147610,"text":"in the context of its breeding ground\nin Arctic National Wildlife Refuge."},{"time":151186,"text":"Well, the wintering ground\nis also critical"},{"time":153432,"text":"and it also is not protected,"},{"time":156057,"text":"and is potentially, could be potentially,\nexploited for gas and mineral rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162855,"text":"The western border of the boreal\nin British Columbia"},{"time":165333,"text":"is marked by the Coast Mountains,"},{"time":166974,"text":"and on the other side of those mountains"},{"time":168969,"text":"is the greatest remaining\ntemperate rainforest in the world,"},{"time":171821,"text":"the Great Bear Rainforest,"},{"time":173187,"text":"and we'll discuss that in a few minutes\nin a bit more detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176071,"text":"All across the boreal,"},{"time":177525,"text":"it's home for a huge incredible range\nof indigenous peoples,"},{"time":182543,"text":"and a rich and varied culture."},{"time":185616,"text":"And I think that one of the reasons"},{"time":188146,"text":"why so many of these groups have\nretained a link to the past,"},{"time":191644,"text":"know their native languages,"},{"time":193680,"text":"the songs, the dances, the traditions,"},{"time":196042,"text":"I think part of that reason\nis because of the remoteness,"},{"time":199577,"text":"the span and the wilderness"},{"time":200903,"text":"of this almost 95 percent\nintact ecosystem."},{"time":205033,"text":"And I think particularly now,"},{"time":206667,"text":"as we see ourselves in a time\nof environmental crisis,"},{"time":209823,"text":"we can learn so much from these people"},{"time":211760,"text":"who have lived so sustainably\nin this ecosystem"},{"time":214009,"text":"for over 10,000 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217496,"text":"In the heart of this ecosystem\nis the very antithesis"},{"time":220557,"text":"of all of these values\nthat we've been talking about,"},{"time":223060,"text":"and I think these\nare some of the core values"},{"time":225222,"text":"that make us proud to be Canadians."},{"time":226924,"text":"This is the Alberta tar sands,"},{"time":228764,"text":"the largest oil reserves on the planet\noutside of Saudi Arabia."},{"time":233390,"text":"Trapped underneath the boreal forest\nand wetlands of northern Alberta"},{"time":237310,"text":"are these vast reserves\nof this sticky, tar-like bitumen."},{"time":241631,"text":"And the mining\nand the exploitation of that"},{"time":244241,"text":"is creating devastation on a scale\nthat the planet has never seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250715,"text":"I want to try to convey\nsome sort of a sense of the size of this."},{"time":254889,"text":"If you look at that truck there,"},{"time":256860,"text":"it is the largest truck\nof its kind on the planet."},{"time":259300,"text":"It is a 400-ton-capacity dump truck"},{"time":262070,"text":"and its dimensions are 45 feet long\nby 35 feet wide and 25 feet high."},{"time":269254,"text":"If I stand beside that truck,"},{"time":270714,"text":"my head comes to around the bottom\nof the yellow part of that hubcap."},{"time":274616,"text":"Within the dimensions of that truck,"},{"time":276709,"text":"you could build a 3,000-square-foot\ntwo-story home quite easily."},{"time":280998,"text":"I did the math."},{"time":282553,"text":"So instead of thinking of that as a truck,\nthink of that as a 3,000-square-foot home."},{"time":287802,"text":"That's not a bad size home."},{"time":289722,"text":"And line those trucks / homes\nback and forth"},{"time":293103,"text":"across there from the bottom\nall the way to the top."},{"time":297993,"text":"And then think of how large\nthat very small section of one mine is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303900,"text":"Now, you can apply that same kind\nof thinking here as well."},{"time":307492,"text":"Now, here you see --\nof course, as you go further on,"},{"time":310225,"text":"these trucks become like a pixel."},{"time":312505,"text":"Again, imagine those\nall back and forth there."},{"time":315921,"text":"How large is that one portion of a mine?"},{"time":319790,"text":"That would be a huge,\nvast metropolitan area,"},{"time":324150,"text":"probably much larger\nthan the city of Victoria."},{"time":326526,"text":"And this is just one of a number of mines,"},{"time":330376,"text":"10 mines so far right now."},{"time":332584,"text":"This is one section of one mining complex,"},{"time":335214,"text":"and there are about another 40 or 50\nin the approval process."},{"time":339077,"text":"No tar sands mine has actually\never been denied approval,"},{"time":341861,"text":"so it is essentially a rubber stamp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345498,"text":"The other method of extraction\nis what's called the in situ."},{"time":348463,"text":"And here, massive amounts of water"},{"time":350459,"text":"are superheated and pumped\nthrough the ground,"},{"time":353490,"text":"through these vasts networks of pipelines,"},{"time":355602,"text":"seismic lines, drill paths,\ncompressor stations."},{"time":359316,"text":"And even though this looks\nmaybe not quite as repugnant as the mines,"},{"time":363483,"text":"it's even more damaging in some ways."},{"time":365684,"text":"It impacts and fragments\na larger part of the wilderness,"},{"time":371083,"text":"where there is 90 percent\nreduction of key species,"},{"time":373569,"text":"like woodland caribou and grizzly bears,"},{"time":375910,"text":"and it consumes\neven more energy, more water,"},{"time":379442,"text":"and produces at least\nas much greenhouse gas."},{"time":382019,"text":"So these in situ developments are at least\nas ecologically damaging as the mines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389717,"text":"The oil produced from either method"},{"time":392382,"text":"produces more greenhouse gas\nemissions than any other oil."},{"time":396958,"text":"This is one of the reasons\nwhy it's called the world's dirtiest oil."},{"time":400596,"text":"It's also one of the reasons"},{"time":401973,"text":"why it is the largest and fastest-growing\nsingle source of carbon in Canada,"},{"time":407193,"text":"and it is also a reason\nwhy Canada is now number three"},{"time":412139,"text":"in terms of producing carbon per person."},{"time":416778,"text":"The tailings ponds are the largest toxic\nimpoundments on the planet."},{"time":422330,"text":"Oil sands -- or rather,\nI should say tar sands --"},{"time":424896,"text":"oil sands is a PR-created term"},{"time":427205,"text":"so that the oil companies\nwouldn't be trying to promote something"},{"time":430288,"text":"that sounds like a sticky tar-like\nsubstance that's the world's dirtiest oil."},{"time":434709,"text":"So they decided to call it oil sands."},{"time":437106,"text":"The tar sands consume more water\nthan any other oil process,"},{"time":440952,"text":"three to five barrels of water\nare taken, polluted"},{"time":444263,"text":"and then returned into tailings ponds,"},{"time":446583,"text":"the largest toxic\nimpoundments on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449084,"text":"SemCrude, just one of the licensees,\nin just one of their tailings ponds,"},{"time":453188,"text":"dumps 250,000 tons\nof this toxic gunk every single day."},{"time":458739,"text":"That's creating the largest toxic\nimpoundments in the history of the planet."},{"time":462756,"text":"So far, this is enough toxin to cover\nthe face of Lake Erie a foot deep."},{"time":469685,"text":"And the tailings ponds\nrange in size up to 9,000 acres."},{"time":474592,"text":"That's two-thirds the size\nof the entire island of Manhattan."},{"time":478565,"text":"That's like from Wall Street\nat the southern edge of Manhattan"},{"time":481558,"text":"up to maybe 120th Street."},{"time":484171,"text":"So this is one of the larger\ntailings ponds."},{"time":488198,"text":"This might be, what? I don't know,\nhalf the size of Manhattan."},{"time":491265,"text":"And you can see in the context,"},{"time":492782,"text":"it's just a relatively small section\nof one of 10 mining complexes"},{"time":497152,"text":"and another 40 to 50\non stream to be approved soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502398,"text":"And of course, these tailings ponds --"},{"time":504978,"text":"well, you can't see\nmany ponds from outer space"},{"time":507557,"text":"and you can see these, so maybe\nwe should stop calling them ponds --"},{"time":511412,"text":"these massive toxic wastelands are built"},{"time":515240,"text":"unlined and on the banks\nof the Athabasca River."},{"time":518562,"text":"And the Athabasca River drains downstream\nto a range of aboriginal communities."},{"time":522971,"text":"In Fort Chipewyan, the 800 people there,\nare finding toxins in the food chain,"},{"time":527309,"text":"this has been scientifically proven."},{"time":529719,"text":"The tar sands toxins\nare in the food chain,"},{"time":531762,"text":"and this is causing cancer\nrates up to 10 times"},{"time":534697,"text":"what they are in the rest of Canada."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537767,"text":"In spite of that, people have to live,\nhave to eat this food in order to survive."},{"time":543264,"text":"The incredibly high price of flying food"},{"time":546303,"text":"into these remote\nNorthern aboriginal communities"},{"time":548916,"text":"and the high rate of unemployment"},{"time":550615,"text":"makes this an absolute\nnecessity for survival."},{"time":553709,"text":"And not that many years ago,\nI was lent a boat by a First Nations man,"},{"time":557813,"text":"and he said, \"When you\ngo out on the river,"},{"time":560064,"text":"do not under any\ncircumstances eat the fish."},{"time":563733,"text":"It's carcinogenic.\""},{"time":565417,"text":"And yet, on the front porch\nof that man's cabin,"},{"time":569962,"text":"I saw four fish."},{"time":571393,"text":"He had to feed his family to survive."},{"time":574193,"text":"And as a parent, I just can't imagine\nwhat that does to your soul."},{"time":580354,"text":"And that's what we're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583893,"text":"The boreal forest\nis also perhaps our best defense"},{"time":588319,"text":"against global warming and climate change."},{"time":591443,"text":"The boreal forest sequesters more carbon\nthan any other terrestrial ecosystem."},{"time":597322,"text":"And this is absolutely key."},{"time":599934,"text":"So what we're doing is,"},{"time":601828,"text":"we're taking the most concentrated\ngreenhouse gas sink --"},{"time":607517,"text":"twice as much greenhouse\ngases are sequestered"},{"time":610074,"text":"in the boreal per acre\nthan the tropical rainforests."},{"time":614088,"text":"And what we're doing is we're destroying"},{"time":616589,"text":"this carbon sink,\nturning it into a carbon bomb."},{"time":619645,"text":"And we're replacing that\nwith the largest industrial project"},{"time":622781,"text":"in the history of the world,"},{"time":624176,"text":"which is producing the most high-carbon\ngreenhouse-gas emitting oil in the world."},{"time":630976,"text":"And we're doing this on the second largest\noil reserves on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636183,"text":"This is one of the reasons why Canada,\noriginally a climate change hero --"},{"time":639984,"text":"we were one of the first\nsignatories of the Kyoto Accord."},{"time":643372,"text":"Now we're the country\nthat has full-time lobbyists"},{"time":645816,"text":"in the European Union and Washington DC,"},{"time":648875,"text":"threatening trade wars"},{"time":650798,"text":"when these countries talk about wanting\nto bring in positive legislation"},{"time":655548,"text":"to limit the import of high-carbon fuels,"},{"time":658583,"text":"of greenhouse gas emissions,\nanything like this,"},{"time":661870,"text":"at international conferences,\nwhether they're in Copenhagen or Cancun,"},{"time":666408,"text":"international conferences\non climate change,"},{"time":668928,"text":"we're the country that gets\nthe dinosaur award every single day,"},{"time":672091,"text":"as being the biggest\nobstacle to progress on this issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677317,"text":"Just 70 miles downstream"},{"time":679747,"text":"is the world's largest freshwater delta,\nthe Peace-Athabasca Delta,"},{"time":683466,"text":"the only one at the juncture\nof all four migratory flyways."},{"time":687293,"text":"This is a globally significant wetland,\nperhaps the greatest on the planet."},{"time":691234,"text":"Incredible habitat\nfor half the bird species"},{"time":694967,"text":"you find in North America, migrating here."},{"time":698611,"text":"And also the last refuge\nfor the largest herd of wild bison,"},{"time":702869,"text":"and also, of course, critical habitat\nfor another whole range of other species."},{"time":707820,"text":"But it too is being threatened"},{"time":709973,"text":"by the massive amount of water\nbeing drawn from the Athabasca,"},{"time":713637,"text":"which feeds these wetlands,"},{"time":715643,"text":"and also the incredible toxic burden"},{"time":717760,"text":"of the largest toxic unlined\nimpoundments on the planet,"},{"time":720557,"text":"which are leaching in to the food chain\nfor all the species downstream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725683,"text":"So as bad as all that is, things are going\nto get much worse -- much, much worse."},{"time":729652,"text":"This is the infrastructure\nas we see it about now."},{"time":733141,"text":"This is what's planned for 2015."},{"time":736110,"text":"And you can see here\nthe Keystone Pipeline,"},{"time":740168,"text":"which would take tar sands raw\ndown to the Gulf Coast,"},{"time":744419,"text":"punching a pipeline through\nthe agricultural heart of North America,"},{"time":748726,"text":"of the United States,"},{"time":751106,"text":"and securing the contract\nwith the dirtiest fuel in the world"},{"time":756435,"text":"by consumption of the United States,"},{"time":759403,"text":"and promoting a huge disincentive"},{"time":762288,"text":"to a sustainable clean-energy\nfuture for America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766140,"text":"Here you see the route\ndown the Mackenzie valley."},{"time":771677,"text":"This would put a pipeline\nto take natural gas from the Beaufort Sea"},{"time":775363,"text":"through the heart of the third largest\nwatershed basin in the world,"},{"time":780051,"text":"and the only one\nwhich is 95 percent intact."},{"time":783231,"text":"And building a pipeline\nwith an industrial highway"},{"time":786639,"text":"would change forever\nthis incredible wilderness,"},{"time":790151,"text":"which is a true rarity\non the planet today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795306,"text":"So the Great Bear Rainforest\nis just over the hill there,"},{"time":799575,"text":"within a few miles,\nwe go from these dry boreal forests"},{"time":802726,"text":"of 100-year-old trees,\nmaybe 10 inches across,"},{"time":806139,"text":"and soon, we're in the coastal\ntemperate rainforest,"},{"time":808600,"text":"rain-drenched, 1,000-year-old trees,"},{"time":812200,"text":"20 feet across, a completely\ndifferent ecosystem."},{"time":815278,"text":"And the Great Bear Rainforest\nis generally considered to be"},{"time":818071,"text":"the largest coastal temperate rainforest\necosystem in the world."},{"time":822014,"text":"Some of the greatest densities"},{"time":823844,"text":"of some of the most iconic\nand threatened species on the planet."},{"time":827881,"text":"And yet there's a proposal,\nof course, to build a pipeline"},{"time":832476,"text":"to take huge tankers,\n10 times the size of the Exxon Valdez,"},{"time":836359,"text":"through some of the most\ndifficult-to-navigate waters in the world,"},{"time":839838,"text":"where only just a few years ago,\na BC ferry ran aground."},{"time":844202,"text":"When one of these tar sands tankers,"},{"time":846579,"text":"carrying the dirtiest oil,\n10 times as much as the Exxon Valdez,"},{"time":849965,"text":"eventually hits a rock and goes down,"},{"time":852298,"text":"we're going to have\none of the worst ecological disasters"},{"time":855232,"text":"this planet has ever seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":857799,"text":"And here we have the plan out to 2030."},{"time":860903,"text":"What they're proposing is an almost\nfour-times increase in production,"},{"time":865480,"text":"and that would industrialize\nan area the size of Florida."},{"time":870271,"text":"In doing so, we'll be removing\na large part of our greatest carbon sink"},{"time":875127,"text":"and replacing it with the most high\ngreenhouse-gas emission oil in the future."},{"time":881581,"text":"The world does not need\nany more tar mines."},{"time":885697,"text":"The world does not need any more pipelines"},{"time":888661,"text":"to wed our addiction to fossil fuels."},{"time":891841,"text":"And the world certainly does not need"},{"time":893857,"text":"the largest toxic impoundments\nto grow and multiply"},{"time":896934,"text":"and further threaten\nthe downstream communities."},{"time":899211,"text":"And let's face it, we all live downstream"},{"time":901231,"text":"in an era of global warming\nand climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905043,"text":"What we need, is we all need to act"},{"time":907825,"text":"to ensure that Canada respects\nthe massive amounts of freshwater"},{"time":912521,"text":"that we hold in this country."},{"time":914956,"text":"We need to ensure\nthat these wetlands and forests"},{"time":917305,"text":"that are our best and greatest\nand most critical defense"},{"time":920611,"text":"against global warming are protected,"},{"time":923097,"text":"and we are not releasing\nthat carbon bomb into the atmosphere."},{"time":927557,"text":"And we need to all gather together\nand say no to the tar sands."},{"time":932712,"text":"And we can do that."},{"time":933887,"text":"there is a huge network\nall over the world,"},{"time":936794,"text":"fighting to stop this project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939040,"text":"And I quite simply think"},{"time":940858,"text":"that this is not something\nthat should be decided just in Canada."},{"time":944748,"text":"Everyone in this room,\neveryone across Canada,"},{"time":947052,"text":"everyone listening to this presentation"},{"time":949037,"text":"has a role to play\nand, I think, a responsibility."},{"time":951863,"text":"Because what we do here\nis going to change our history,"},{"time":957522,"text":"it's going to color\nour possibility to survive,"},{"time":960239,"text":"and for our children to survive\nand have a rich future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":965749,"text":"We have an incredible gift in the boreal,"},{"time":967735,"text":"an incredible opportunity to preserve\nour best defense against global warming,"},{"time":972987,"text":"but we could let that slip away."},{"time":975715,"text":"The tar sands could threaten\nnot just a large section of the boreal."},{"time":979717,"text":"It compromises the life and the health"},{"time":982714,"text":"of some of our most underprivileged\nand vulnerable people,"},{"time":987262,"text":"the aboriginal communities\nthat have so much to teach us."},{"time":991131,"text":"It could destroy the Athabasca Delta,"},{"time":993733,"text":"the largest and possibly greatest\nfreshwater delta in the planet."},{"time":998389,"text":"It could destroy\nthe Great Bear Rainforest,"},{"time":1001982,"text":"the largest temperate\nrainforest in the world."},{"time":1004817,"text":"And it could have huge impacts"},{"time":1006849,"text":"on the future of the agricultural\nheartland of North America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011337,"text":"I hope that you will all,\nif you've been moved by this presentation,"},{"time":1014555,"text":"join with the growing\ninternational community"},{"time":1017358,"text":"to get Canada to step up\nto its responsibilities,"},{"time":1020828,"text":"to convince Canada to go back\nto being a climate change champion"},{"time":1025238,"text":"instead of a climate change villain,"},{"time":1026995,"text":"and to say no to the tar sands,"},{"time":1028676,"text":"and yes to a clean energy future for all."},{"time":1031369,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1032717,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}